    static &lt;T&gt; int carHelper(List&lt;T&gt; elements) {
        int count = 0;
        for (T element : elements) {
            count += element.getWheel();
        }
        return count;
    }
But in the case you will get compile-time error at *element.getWheel()* because T type is some unknown type. Compiler does not know about his methods. To find some generic solution we have to define boundary for method parameters. Let&#39;s say input parameters will be Vehicle or it&#39;s children. In Vehicle class, let&#39;s say, we will introduce needed fields and his descendants will inherit them. In the case below listed method will work. Read about [wildcards][1] in generics.

    static  int carHelper(List&lt;? extends Car&gt; elements) {
        int count = 0;
        for (Car element : elements) {
            count += element.getWheels();
        }
        return count;
    }


